Integral How-To
===============
***

First:
------

Simplify

Second:
-------

Know basic formulas

Third
-----

Classify:

 * if a prod of trig funcs, use methods of Sec. 7.2
 * if power func, try Integration by parts
 * for rational functions, do division/partial fractions
 * if $\sqrt{\pm x^2\pm a^2}$ try trig subsitution

Fourth:
-------

Be clever

$$
\begin{align}
\int\frac{1}{1-\sin x}\ dx = \int \frac{1}{1-\sin x} * \frac{1+\sin x}{1+\sin x}\ dx\\
\text{...}\\
\end{align}
$$
